WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:01.560
Hey, good morning, family.

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:01.328
Thank you for joining us again today.

00:00:01.912 --> 00:00:06.000
We're going to pray over your needs today.

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:09.920
There are many of you, like this family right here, who are believing for so much.

00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:13.536
We received that in the mail today, and I'm just like, 'Wow.

00:00:13.536 --> 00:00:20.806
' There are so many of you believing for a breakthrough for your loved ones.

00:00:21.729 --> 00:00:24.960
I mean, I have other photos right here.

00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:26.320
There are so many families.

00:00:26.320 --> 00:00:30.400
Like I said, we have photos now all over our car.

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:36.160
We drive around and look like we have photos everywhere that we pray over when we're driving around.

00:00:36.568 --> 00:00:40.240
People send them to us, and they need a breakthrough.

00:00:40.240 --> 00:00:47.280
These people are desperate; they need a touch from the Father.

00:00:47.280 --> 00:00:53.280
They don't need a stale word from a pastor where you go on a Wednesday night or a Sunday and you walk away thinking, 'What was that?

00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:57.760
Why did I waste my thirty minutes?

00:00:57.760 --> 00:01:00.960
Why did I waste an hour?

00:01:00.960 --> 00:01:04.015
I could have gotten more watching a YouTube video than I got from that.

00:01:04.015 --> 00:01:06.560
' I don't want to waste people's time.

00:01:06.560 --> 00:01:08.545
I say, 'God, we need a fresh river.

00:01:08.545 --> 00:01:11.193
We need fresh glory.

00:01:11.193 --> 00:01:19.040
' We need to get this old vinegar out of these old wineskins and put the anointing of the Holy Ghost on us.

00:01:19.040 --> 00:01:26.560
Rub that oil down into that pouch of who we are, that vessel, making it pliable again.

00:01:26.560 --> 00:01:39.760
Because when you put that anointing oil on that vessel and rub it in, making that leather pouch pliable again, it makes it so if you put the new wine in it, it won't crack and bust.

00:01:40.544 --> 00:01:47.600
The oil and the anointing of the Holy Ghost is what makes us brand new every single day.

00:01:47.600 --> 00:01:55.360
You have to have that glory—the outward honey glow.

00:01:55.360 --> 00:02:06.560
That's why I told Diana—we talk about it all the time—I want it so much that it never turns off, that they have to put a drape around my head because people ask, 'What is going on with that dude's face?

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:08.310
He's glowing with the glory.

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:13.244
' I tell my children, 'We represent the Father.

00:02:13.244 --> 00:02:16.480
' So, we act like the Father; we demonstrate ourselves as the Father would.

00:02:16.480 --> 00:02:20.080
I know we're all a work in progress, but I'm just desperate for Him.

00:02:20.080 --> 00:02:22.347
I'm desperate for Him.

00:02:22.347 --> 00:02:26.124
And I know what's coming.

00:02:26.880 --> 00:02:30.380
I know a great shaking is coming to awaken you.

00:02:32.800 --> 00:02:38.750
And I will sound the alarm, just like Jeremiah, to tell you all that God is coming.

00:02:50.020 --> 00:02:50.920
And you have to get your house in order because we're running out of time.

00:02:50.920 --> 00:02:57.640
Thank God we're not like we were back then; we're under more grace.

00:03:05.840 --> 00:03:10.390
I get it, but I'm telling you all, a great shaking is coming.

00:03:05.840 --> 00:03:07.940
What's coming is not God's judgment.

00:03:05.840 --> 00:03:11.840
Ladies and gentlemen, what's coming is not judgment; it's a Father correcting a child who is spoiled.

00:03:11.840 --> 00:03:23.120
It's the Father who is correcting a child who has gone wayward, saying, 'You've gone off the road, buddy, and I want you to come back over here in the fold.

00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:31.760
' The ninety-nine sheep are over here, and you're the one, and I'm trying to snatch that one.

00:03:31.760 --> 00:03:36.960
There are a lot of ones, but He's trying to grab a hold of those ones.

00:03:39.480 --> 00:03:44.153
And He's like, 'You got way off track, and you're fifty miles away from where you're supposed to be.

00:03:44.153 --> 00:03:50.960
But I have more mercy and more love to let you have an extended time to bring them in.

00:03:50.960 --> 00:03:59.760
' Your unsaved loved ones—the people who are so wayward that you think, 'Man, they're never coming in.

00:03:59.760 --> 00:04:02.220
' No, all things are possible to him who believes.

00:04:02.220 --> 00:04:06.320
Ladies and gentlemen, glory to God!

00:04:06.320 --> 00:04:08.432
All things are possible to him who believes.

00:04:08.432 --> 00:04:11.600
You've just got to believe it.

00:04:11.600 --> 00:04:12.213
You've got to put your faith into motion.

00:04:12.213 --> 00:04:17.120
What are you believing for today?

00:04:17.120 --> 00:04:19.570
You say, 'Well, I'm believing for finances.

00:04:17.120 --> 00:04:21.440
' Then sow a seed.

00:04:21.440 --> 00:04:22.880
Every seed produces after its own kind.

00:04:37.340 --> 00:04:37.880
What are you believing God for today?

00:04:37.880 --> 00:04:38.960
David said, 'I give nothing that doesn't cost me something.

00:04:38.960 --> 00:04:45.920
If it doesn't cost you something, then it isn't precious to you.

00:04:45.920 --> 00:04:51.920
' And David gave when it hurt, and the Bible says that.

00:04:51.920 --> 00:04:54.288
And that's where I've tried to say, 'What's my chokehold?

00:04:54.288 --> 00:04:57.840
Where am I at with the Lord concerning this?

00:04:57.840 --> 00:05:03.520
' People say, 'I don't believe in tithing because it's under the Old Covenant.

00:05:03.520 --> 00:05:07.168
' I believe in giving God something to work with.

00:05:07.168 --> 00:05:16.160
I believe in giving God—if the farmer sows a seed to reap a harvest, then I'm going to sow a seed to reap a harvest.

00:05:16.160 --> 00:05:21.520
If I have a need, I sow a seed.

00:05:34.853 --> 00:05:35.307
That's what we always do in this household.

00:05:35.307 --> 00:05:37.573
Where do you give?

00:05:38.480 --> 00:05:40.580
You give to your local church.

00:05:38.480 --> 00:05:41.591
You give to where you're being fed spiritually.

00:05:41.591 --> 00:05:47.472
You give to the people who are pouring into you spiritually; that's where you give.

00:05:47.472 --> 00:05:53.709
So, where your pastor is and where the people are who are ministering to you on a day-to-day basis—those are the people you give to.

00:05:53.709 --> 00:05:54.698
Why?

00:05:54.698 --> 00:05:58.160
Because that's what keeps the local church going.

00:06:03.632 --> 00:06:04.288
If you don't have a local church in your area, you have to have a prayer covering.

00:06:04.288 --> 00:06:07.568
That's what changes things.

00:06:07.568 --> 00:06:11.627
When that body comes together, you come as an army in that community.

00:06:11.627 --> 00:06:17.120
So, you keep that local church going.

00:06:25.900 --> 00:06:26.850
You keep the people who are feeding you going so that they keep feeding you, so they are able to distribute out and help others.

00:06:26.850 --> 00:06:31.600
It's like a storehouse.

00:06:31.600 --> 00:06:32.169
You bring your tithe to the storehouse.

00:06:32.169 --> 00:06:36.720
You bring that to the storehouse.

00:06:36.720 --> 00:06:37.549
Where the storehouse is, is where you're getting fed.

00:06:37.549 --> 00:06:41.280
That's where the grain is, and all the things you put in the storehouse.

00:06:51.200 --> 00:06:53.650
You bring the tithe to the storehouse.

00:06:51.200 --> 00:06:55.920
Your local church is your storehouse where you're getting fed.

00:06:55.920 --> 00:07:03.120
You take care of that pastor; you take care of them, and then you make sure they're able to have community outreach or whatever they're doing.

00:07:03.120 --> 00:07:10.340
I just believe that that's what we do in these last days to help the local church out.

00:07:13.280 --> 00:07:14.330
We help it.

00:07:13.280 --> 00:07:17.120
You say, 'Well, we don't have to tithe.

00:07:17.120 --> 00:07:18.560
' No, but you still give.

00:07:19.872 --> 00:07:30.960
I don't believe there's a curse on people if you don't tithe, okay, but I believe that God said He rebukes the devourer for our sake.

00:07:37.840 --> 00:07:41.690
And if He did it back then, He'll do it again.

00:07:49.968 --> 00:07:50.472
And I want a blessing on my money.

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:58.267
I want prosperity and His blessing on it—my heart hearing Him say, 'Brandon, well done, thou good and faithful servant.

00:07:58.800 --> 00:08:03.664
You did everything you could; you helped stretch the Kingdom of God throughout the whole world.

00:08:03.664 --> 00:08:05.840
' Most people don't want to give.

00:08:05.840 --> 00:08:14.800
Most people are stingy with it, and they say, 'Well, when I get more money, I'll give and do this and that.

00:08:14.800 --> 00:08:18.720
' No, we started tithing because we had to.

00:08:18.720 --> 00:08:26.160
I don't know why I got off on this; I guess it's because Braden told me something.

00:08:26.160 --> 00:08:34.080
We get some emails where people say, 'We don't believe in tithing.

00:08:41.520 --> 00:08:43.632
What do you believe about it?

00:08:43.632 --> 00:08:48.560
' Well, this is my opinion: I believe in tithing.

00:08:58.000 --> 00:09:00.450
I believe in giving my ten percent.

00:09:00.440 --> 00:09:06.371
I believe in giving over the ten percent as much as I can because I know what it takes to get the gospel out.

00:09:19.120 --> 00:09:22.620
It seems like I've worked for churches my whole life.

00:09:27.547 --> 00:09:29.120
We knew what it took to get the bills paid at the church; we knew what it took to get the flyers out and all the staff paid.

00:09:29.120 --> 00:09:30.288
It takes millions of dollars.

00:09:30.288 --> 00:09:34.960
Most people say, 'Well, I gave my ten bucks.

00:09:34.960 --> 00:09:42.480
' Well, the church was thankful for the ten dollars, but there were a lot of tippers.

00:09:42.480 --> 00:09:53.040
You're believing that you can step into the overflow, for God to speak to you about abundant things, but that comes out of whether He can trust you with it.

00:09:53.040 --> 00:10:01.227
If God can't trust you with the ten percent that you have to tithe to Him, He's not going to show you the greater works.

00:10:01.227 --> 00:10:04.160
I'm telling you, I'm just being real with you all.

00:10:04.160 --> 00:10:10.640
I'm just telling you all the facts, and most people don't want to hear it.

00:10:20.640 --> 00:10:21.160
You say, 'Well, I'm qualified because I gave my five bucks to the Lord today.

00:10:21.160 --> 00:10:22.578
' You tipped God.

00:10:24.375 --> 00:10:27.520
You made a quarter of a million dollars last year, and you gave ten dollars.

00:10:27.520 --> 00:10:27.933
Whoop-de-do!

00:10:31.653 --> 00:10:32.067
I mean, I'm just saying.

00:10:42.036 --> 00:10:42.507
You think that you're qualified for God to tell you the secret things because you gave your hundred bucks and you made $250,000 last year?

00:10:42.507 --> 00:10:43.920
Seriously, it comes out of sacrifice.

00:10:43.920 --> 00:10:48.138
David said, 'I didn't give God anything that didn't cost me something.

00:10:48.138 --> 00:10:55.200
' So you are expecting God to pour out his blessing on you in a dump truck load, but you gave in a thimble load.

00:10:55.200 --> 00:11:03.600
And you're asking God to do something mightily in your finances whenever it's so backwards is what I'm trying to tell y'all.

00:11:03.600 --> 00:11:09.947
Seek ye first the kingdom and his righteousness, and all these things will be added unto you.

00:11:15.600 --> 00:11:23.650
Give, and it shall be given unto you: good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over will men give into your bosom.

00:11:20.320 --> 00:11:23.470
And so that's just what Diana and I believe.

00:11:20.320 --> 00:11:25.040
You ask us or tell you, I don't like talking about money stuff because you're like, 'Well, you know you're after money.

00:11:25.040 --> 00:11:30.400
' No, I don't care; I honest to goodness don't care.

00:11:40.320 --> 00:11:44.870
This is because people ask me, 'What do you believe about this, Brandon?

00:11:40.320 --> 00:11:41.367
' And this is what Diana and I believe.

00:11:41.367 --> 00:11:46.080
We believe in the power of the seed.

00:11:46.080 --> 00:11:55.265
We believe in the power that you give and it shall be given unto you: good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over will men give into your bosom.

00:11:55.265 --> 00:11:57.680
That's what Diana and I believe.

00:11:57.680 --> 00:12:04.080
We believe that God is a rewarder of those that diligently seek Him.

00:12:04.080 --> 00:12:07.824
Not just with my time and prayer, but seeking Him with my finances.

00:12:07.824 --> 00:12:12.409
God, if I give, you said that you give me 30, 60, 100-fold.

00:12:14.778 --> 00:12:15.127
That's what you said in your word.

00:12:22.903 --> 00:12:24.149
You said in Malachi—I'm not putting myself underneath the old covenant, Lord—but you said back then that you rebuke the devourer for my sake.

00:12:24.149 --> 00:12:28.647
So Father, how much more will you rebuke the devourer for my sake now?

00:12:32.160 --> 00:12:34.887
I'm not underneath the old covenant, but I'm underneath the new, but I still want to believe in the blessing.

00:12:35.433 --> 00:12:38.160
I still want to believe in helping the church out.

00:12:55.004 --> 00:12:55.425
And it's a heart thing.

00:12:58.800 --> 00:12:59.413
It's a heart thing.

00:13:04.320 --> 00:13:07.411
And I say, 'God, my heart is for you.

00:13:07.411 --> 00:13:11.120
My heart is for the gospel.

00:13:11.120 --> 00:13:16.422
I want to help Billy Burke out.

00:13:16.422 --> 00:13:17.600
I want to help missionaries out.

00:13:17.600 --> 00:13:18.880
I want to help them.

00:13:18.880 --> 00:13:27.840
' If you're going out and praying for the sick and seeing people recover, I would like to help you.

00:13:31.680 --> 00:13:32.928
If I see that you're doing something major for God, I want to help you.

00:13:37.920 --> 00:13:42.820
I see the cause, I see the anointing, and you sow into the anointing.

00:13:53.648 --> 00:13:54.520
Do you give all at one place?

00:13:54.520 --> 00:13:58.880
No, I split my seed a lot of times and I help each ministry out.

00:13:58.880 --> 00:14:06.400
I help pastors, prophets, teachers, evangelists, and all this.

00:14:19.856 --> 00:14:20.784
And I try, even if it's just five bucks whatever, until you grow.

00:14:20.784 --> 00:14:22.640
You say, 'Here, here, here.

00:14:22.640 --> 00:14:26.960
' But I try to sow the big one.

00:14:32.144 --> 00:14:40.144
And then the one that feeds me the most I give them the most, right, because I'm getting impartation from it.

00:14:40.144 --> 00:14:41.280
Above tithe I try to help out.

00:14:41.280 --> 00:14:45.696
So that's what I'm trying to say.

00:14:51.280 --> 00:14:53.840
And maybe that'll make sense for some of y'all, but you ask me my opinion, what Diana and I do.

00:14:53.840 --> 00:14:55.940
And that's exactly what we've done.

00:14:53.840 --> 00:15:00.352
And we've done it for a while now saying, 'God help me because I'm not going to be manipulated.

00:15:00.352 --> 00:15:11.200
' 'Well, all your tithe should come to my church because you're a part of my flock and you need to give all your money here.

00:15:11.200 --> 00:15:17.200
' Whatever I'm going to do, I'm going to do what the Holy Spirit tells me to do.

00:15:17.200 --> 00:15:19.280
And people get ticked off about that, but whatever.

00:15:28.640 --> 00:15:32.490
I just follow the voice of the Lord for our life.

00:15:34.640 --> 00:15:38.490
And what he tells me to do is I give it.

00:15:34.640 --> 00:15:45.360
If you're not underneath the curse of the old covenant and it's not there, then I'm not going to be manipulated about my tithe either.

00:15:45.360 --> 00:15:51.520
I will not sit there and have you tell me all this stuff where I should be giving my money.

00:15:51.520 --> 00:15:55.600
I will follow the Holy Spirit and he will show me that which is to come.

00:15:55.600 --> 00:16:01.360
And when you do that and you're led by the Holy Spirit you'll always be blessed.

00:16:01.360 --> 00:16:06.720
Follow the Holy Spirit in what the word tells you to do.

00:16:06.720 --> 00:16:08.000
Give to where you're being fed.

00:16:08.000 --> 00:16:13.120
Give to the ministries that are feeding you.

00:16:27.840 --> 00:16:28.424
And I'm telling you, God will anoint you.

00:16:28.424 --> 00:16:33.680
Be led by the spirit of God when it comes to your giving.

00:16:33.680 --> 00:16:38.800
There's a lot of different theories; there's a lot of different theologies when it comes to this.

00:16:41.200 --> 00:16:43.600
And everybody's about it because everybody wants the money.

00:16:46.512 --> 00:16:47.760
And I'll be real with you, that's what I've seen a lot in the body of Christ.

00:16:58.800 --> 00:17:00.000
A lot of people want the money and they go, 'I feel that if you give this $58 seed and this $58 blessing you're going to get a miracle.

00:17:00.000 --> 00:17:03.173
' I don't get into all that stuff.

00:17:03.173 --> 00:17:09.707
I just give where I'm led to give to help when God tells me to give.

00:17:25.440 --> 00:17:29.600
And that's exactly what Diana and I do.

00:17:29.600 --> 00:17:30.418
And I am not manipulated by emotion.

00:17:30.418 --> 00:17:35.324
Never give out of emotion.

00:17:35.324 --> 00:17:37.707
Give by the spirit of the Lord leading you.

00:17:37.707 --> 00:17:41.440
Does that make sense?

00:17:41.440 --> 00:17:45.744
If you're led by your emotions, your emotions change all the time.

00:17:48.496 --> 00:17:54.618
You can give a seed and you'll be like, 'Why in the world did I just give that?

00:17:54.618 --> 00:17:58.000
' five minutes later.

00:17:58.000 --> 00:18:03.760
Sometimes it's the devil trying to torment you, but sometimes it is because you acted out in flesh.

00:18:04.488 --> 00:18:13.776
And I'm not going to be, 'Well, you know, I heard the sob story about that and it was really sad at church and I gave it.

00:18:13.776 --> 00:18:15.600
' I'm not going to give out of emotion.

00:18:15.600 --> 00:18:22.720
I'm giving by the spirit of God leading me.

00:18:22.720 --> 00:18:24.120
Does that make sense?

00:18:22.720 --> 00:18:28.800
When you're led by the spirit of the Lord there is a blessing behind it.

00:18:28.800 --> 00:18:31.636
But there truly is a 30, 60, and 100-fold.

00:18:31.636 --> 00:18:35.040
And you find the 100-fold grounds, you found a nugget.

00:18:35.040 --> 00:18:39.807
If you find the 60-fold, you still found a really good one.

00:18:39.807 --> 00:18:40.240
Thirty is okay; it's a return.

00:18:40.240 --> 00:18:46.560
But I'm serious, I told the Lord, I said, 'Where is the 100-fold ground?

00:18:46.560 --> 00:18:51.680
Show me how to sow into that because I want to be the farmer that sows into the manure that gets back the big harvest.

00:18:53.338 --> 00:18:55.549
I sow to reap, I sow.

00:18:55.549 --> 00:18:57.760
' They said, 'Well, do you give to get?

00:18:57.760 --> 00:19:02.080
' Well, yeah, basically, but I'm not giving it out of that attitude.

00:19:02.080 --> 00:19:08.080
I'm giving to sow because God says he loves a cheerful giver, but he gives back 30, 60.

00:19:08.080 --> 00:19:09.130
It's his system.

00:19:08.080 --> 00:19:14.080
So I'm sowing into it saying, 'God, show me how to reap the maximum reward.

00:19:14.080 --> 00:19:15.024
' And if this is stony ground, run.

00:19:15.024 --> 00:19:17.384
'Well, their ministry died.

00:19:17.384 --> 00:19:18.800
' Well, it wasn't me, it's stony ground.

00:19:19.328 --> 00:19:21.440
It doesn't need to be there anyway.

00:19:28.400 --> 00:19:28.880
I mean, I'm just being real.

00:19:28.880 --> 00:19:29.360
Let them move on and do something else.

00:19:29.360 --> 00:19:36.167
Sell on eBay; it's a good living.

00:19:36.167 --> 00:19:41.173
If their ground is stony they shouldn't be in ministry anyway.

00:19:41.173 --> 00:19:46.080
If it's sandy soil and it's bad soil, why are they preaching then?

00:19:46.080 --> 00:19:52.400
Close the doors down and go on.

00:19:57.008 --> 00:19:58.160
We need people that are filled with and controlled by the Holy Ghost in these last days.

00:19:58.160 --> 00:20:04.800
We don't need to be wasting people's time just doing it because it's all that I've ever known how to do.

00:20:04.800 --> 00:20:05.850
Do something else.

00:20:04.800 --> 00:20:06.528
Be a door greeter at Walmart.

00:20:08.256 --> 00:20:10.560
I mean, I don't mean to be rude but that's just real.

00:20:10.560 --> 00:20:12.613
Don't waste my time.

00:20:12.613 --> 00:20:16.720
And that's why I don't want to waste your time.

00:20:16.720 --> 00:20:17.396
We're just real.

00:20:17.396 --> 00:20:20.773
I've seen it all.

00:20:20.773 --> 00:20:23.884
I've been around some big ministers, some of the big guys.

00:20:27.680 --> 00:20:28.338
And you look at them and you go, 'What's real and what's not?

00:20:28.338 --> 00:20:33.600
Is there an anointing here or not?

00:20:33.600 --> 00:20:34.920
' I want you all to be successful.

00:20:49.840 --> 00:20:57.540
I want you to go from glory to glory and not keep going around the mountain expecting different results every single time.

00:20:49.840 --> 00:20:51.893
For 40 years they wandered in the wilderness.

00:20:51.893 --> 00:21:00.088
For 40 years they wandered and they never said, 'Why am I still going through what we're going through?

00:21:00.088 --> 00:21:01.840
' 'Moses, why are we still walking around this mountain?

00:21:01.840 --> 00:21:22.400
' And you go through another year and he's like, 'Well, the whole generation has to die because of unbelief and we're going to raise up the Joshuas and the Calebs to go and take the land because we really aren't the size of grasshoppers to these giants.

